   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[= Action name =
PCK.AUTOMIC_TOMCAT.PUB.ACTION.RESTART_APPLICATION

= General description =
This Action will restart web application on Tomcat

= Inputs =
- Tomcat Base URL*                         : Provide URL pointing to your Tomcat installation. E.g. http://localhost:8080/
- Manager app*                             : Provide name of the manager application, which is usually called "manager". E.g. manager
- Context path*                            : The context path (including the leading slash) of the web application you are dealing with. To select the ROOT web application, specify "/". E.g. /myapp
- username*                                : Username used to manage Tomcat. The user needs the role "manage-script" role assigned. E.g tomcat.
- password*                                : Password used to manage Tomcat.

Note => Tomcat version should be 7 or above

= Failure Conditions =
If the user provides invalid Tomcat Base URL or invalid manager app or  "\" in context path.

= Behavior =
(none)

=Return Value=
(none)

= Outputs =
* Return code is 0 in case of success.
* Return code is non-zero in case of failure.

= Rollback =
(none)

= Logging =
AE logs will be displayed in the AE report.

= Example =
- Tomcat Base URL                           : http://localhost:8080/
- Manager app                               : manager
- Context path*                             : /myapp
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
]]></Docu>
